 {"id":"coding_agent_session_search-pkw","title":"P1.4 Add provenance fields to Tantivy schema","description":"# P1.4 Add provenance fields to Tantivy schema

## Overview
Extend the Tantivy search index schema to include provenance fields,
enabling efficient filtering by source.

## Implementation Details

### Schema Extension
In `src/search/tantivy.rs`:
```rust
fn build_schema() -> Schema {
    let mut schema_builder = Schema::builder();

    // ... existing fields

    // Provenance fields
    schema_builder.add_text_field("source_id", STRING | STORED);
    schema_builder.add_text_field("origin_kind", STRING | STORED);  // "local" | "ssh"
    schema_builder.add_text_field("origin_host", STRING | STORED);  // nullable display label

    // Optional: workspace_original for path rewriting audit
    schema_builder.add_text_field("workspace_original", STORED);  // Not indexed, just stored

    schema_builder.build()
}
```

### IMPORTANT: Schema Version Bump
To enable safe rollback and debugging, bump the Tantivy index directory version:

```rust
// Current: index stored in <data_dir>/tantivy_v1/
// New: index stored in <data_dir>/tantivy_v2/
pub const TANTIVY_INDEX_VERSION: &str = "tantivy_v2";

pub fn index_dir(data_dir: &Path) -> PathBuf {
    data_dir.join(TANTIVY_INDEX_VERSION)
}
```

Also bump SCHEMA_HASH:
```rust
pub const SCHEMA_HASH: &str = "v2_with_provenance";
```

This allows:
- Old v1 index remains for rollback if needed
- Users can downgrade without data loss
- Clear signal that schema changed

### Document Building
When adding documents:
```rust
fn build_doc(&self, conv: &NormalizedConversation, msg: &NormalizedMessage) -> Document {
    let mut doc = Document::new();

    // ... existing fields

    // Provenance
    if let Some(origin) = &conv.origin {
        doc.add_text(self.source_id_field, &origin.source_id);
        doc.add_text(self.origin_kind_field, origin.kind.as_str());
        if let Some(host) = &origin.host {
            doc.add_text(self.origin_host_field, host);
        }
    } else {
        // Legacy data defaults to local
        doc.add_text(self.source_id_field, LOCAL_SOURCE_ID);
        doc.add_text(self.origin_kind_field, "local");
    }

    doc
}
```

### Query Filtering
```rust
fn build_source_filter_query(&self, filter: &SourceFilter) -> Box<dyn Query> {
    match filter {
        SourceFilter::All => Box::new(AllQuery),
        SourceFilter::Local => {
            let term = Term::from_field_text(self.origin_kind_field, "local");
            Box::new(TermQuery::new(term, IndexRecordOption::Basic))
        }
        SourceFilter::Remote => {
            // Match anything that's NOT local
            let local_term = Term::from_field_text(self.origin_kind_field, "local");
            Box::new(BooleanQuery::new(vec![
                (Occur::MustNot, Box::new(TermQuery::new(local_term, IndexRecordOption::Basic))),
            ]))
        }
        SourceFilter::Hostname(h) => {
            let term = Term::from_field_text(self.source_id_field, h);
            Box::new(TermQuery::new(term, IndexRecordOption::Basic))
        }
    }
}
```

